Hungary to Announce Home-Loan Subsidy Plan Today, Nemzet Reports

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 
2011-10-12T06:42:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-12/hungary-to-announce-home-loan-subsidy-plan-today-nemzet-reports.html
Hungarian Prime Minister  Viktor Orban  may announce a home-loan subsidy plan, Magyar Nemzet
reported today, citing an unidentified person.  The plan may include aid to families with children for
their home purchases and interest-rate subsidies for borrowers
who fell behind on their mortgage payments by more than 90 days,
the daily newspaper said. Economy Minister  Gyorgy Matolcsy  has
already said next yearâ€™s budget may allocate 6.5 billion forint
($30 million) for the plan.  Orban and Matolcsy will brief reporters on a home-loan plan
at 11 a.m. in Budapest.  To contact the reporter on this story:
